California ignition interlock device laws & requirements  Approved by the State of California: Intoxalock Legacy Intoxalock eLERT 24  We have over 20 years of experience helping people just like you install an ignition interlock device in California and regain your driver's license after a DUI. Don’t let the thought of installing a ignition interlock (BAIID, IID, car breathalyzer, interlock system) intimidate you. Our law specialists will answer all of your ignition interlock questions and walk you through the State of California requirements and laws, help you find a local authorized installation location and schedule an installation to regain your license the fastest way possible. Intoxalock ignition interlock device benefits in California:  One month FREE* in California FREE ignition interlock device installation after rebate* More service centers in California than any competitor Affordable ignition interlock pricing and financial assistance available 24/7 customer service support Over 1,800 convenient locations nationwide The fastest way to get back on the road legally in CA      Additional drunk driving resources:    Home alcohol monitoring    Help a friend     Find an attorney    Find treatment center  State of California website  State of California ignition interlock & drunk driving laws:     First Offense DUI | Second Offense DUI | Third Offense DUI | Court Order     California ignition interlock brochure (PDF)  First offense DUI If you have been convicted of a first offense DUI in California, your license will be suspended for a minimum of six months. Depending on the circumstances of your arrest, you may be eligible immediately to apply for restricted driving privileges.  To apply for your restricted driving privileges, you will need to:  Pay a fine ranging from $390 to $1,000 Serve 48 hours to six months in jail Prove financial responsibility Provide proof of enrollment in a licensed driving-under-the-influence program  Top   Second offense DUI If you have been convicted of a DUI in California, your license will be suspended for two to three years depending on the circumstances of your arrest. However, you may be eligible to regain your restricted driving privileges within 90 days. Alcohol only (No injury)  Two year suspension Eligible after 90 days  Alcohol only (With injury)  Three year suspension Eligible after one year  Drugs with or without alcohol (No injury)  Two year suspension Eligible after one year  Drugs with or without alcohol (With injury)  Three year suspension Eligible after one year  To apply for your restricted driving privileges, you will need to:  Install an ignition interlock device Pay all fines including, but not limited to a DUI penalty ranging from $390 to $1,000 and a $15 restriction fee Provide proof of enrollment into an 18 month licensed driving-under-the-influence program or a 30 month program if available in your area  Provide proof of SR22 insurance or proof of financial responsibility Clear all other outstanding suspensions and revocations on your driving record  Top    Third offense DUI  If you have been convicted of a third offense DUI in California, your license will be suspended for three to five years depending on the circumstances of your arrest. However, you may be eligible to regain your restricted driving privileges within six months. Alcohol only (No injury)  Three year suspension Eligible after six months  Alcohol only (With injury)  Five year suspension Eligible after one year  Drugs with or without alcohol (No injury)  Three year suspension Eligible after one year  Drugs with or without alcohol (With injury)  Five year suspension Eligible after one year  To apply for your restricted driving privileges, you will need to:  Install an ignition interlock device Pay all fines including, but not limited to a DUI penalty ranging from $390 to $1,000 and a $15 restriction fee  Provide proof of enrollment into an 18 month licensed driving-under-the-influence program or a 30 month program if available in your area  Provide proof of SR22 insurance or proof of financial responsibility Clear all other outstanding suspensions and revocations on your driving record Install an ignition interlock device  Top   Court order The court may order you to install an IID with or without a Department of Motor Vehicle (DMV) requirement. You will be provided with a court order at the time of your hearing and it will specify if you need to install your IID and may outline how long you will need it. Installing an IID as a requirement for a court order does not give you driving privileges. To be eligible to drive, you must have a restricted driver’s license through the California DMV. Top    Financial assistance for ignition interlocks in California The state of California provides financial aid for low income drivers who might not be able to afford an ignition interlock device. Find out if you qualify for financial assistance.Top   *Mention code CAOFFER for free install and free month promotions. Customer must pay ignition interlock installation costs to installation location at the time of install. Installation location will provide rebate form and upon remittance, the customer's account will be credited for their installation up to $100. Specialty vehicles may require higher ignition interlock installation fees. First month free credit will be deducted from start-up costs. Valid only on leases five months or longer. Not valid on voluntary leases. California customers only.This information is provided as a guideline only. Each case will vary.























