How much does an ignition interlock cost? An ignition interlock device costs as little as $2.15 a day and is an affordable way to prevent drunk driving. Interlock devices usually cost less than a daily cup of coffee or a fast food sandwich. Your overall price covers a variety of things that could include the device itself, a camera unit if required, mouthpieces, installation, removal, calibrations, reporting, device maintenance and more. Your total ignition interlock device cost will vary depending on a variety of factors:  The state ordering your ignition interlock device installation Additional features you are required to have (camera, GPS, real-time reporting) The length of time you are required to have an ignition interlock device installed The year, make and model of the vehicle you are installing your ignition interlock device in 
Intoxalock ignition interlock pricing
Intoxalock promises to always provide customers with the lowest prices available. With cost-saving specials like free installations and free first month leases available in many states, we are committed to making the ignition interlock process affordable. If there isn’t a current offer in your state, we are usually committed to already providing pricing much lower than other providers. Check your state for special offers.
State financial assistance for ignition interlock devices Many states offer financial assistance for customers needing an interlock that meet certain qualifications. Many times, those requirements are determined by the courts. Our state interlock specialists can help you determine if you qualify for financial aid to help cover your ignition interlock cost.
Ignition interlock devices prevent repeat drunk driving offenses
An alcohol-related driving offense (DUI, DWI, OWI) is extremely expensive. Ignition interlock devices are proven to be the most effective method at reducing repeat offenses. According to MADD, there's a 67% reduction of repeat drunk driving offenses when comparing those with an interlock device installed to those with a license suspension. Read more drunk driving facts here.
The national average cost of a DUI/DWI/OWI is around $10,000. Read more about the costs associated with a DUI. 
Monthly lease pricing and installation costs vary by state. For a free, no obligation pricing quote, call us at (888) 283-5899 or submit your information below.  Read more about ignition interlock device pricing on the Intoxalock blog.

 




 



